WorkItem.Description:
Not all browsers (IE < 9) have a window.console object available, so it's necessary to check for its existence before using it. Otherwise, you'll get an error like the following:

Message: 'console' is undefined
Line: 134
Char: 17
Code: 0
URI: /js/jquery.rateit.js

This error was observed in IE8, which _does_ have a console, but it's undefined unless the developer tools are open.
WorkItem.Summary: Need to check for window.console before using it

Comments.Message: Thanks for reporting the issue. The console.log slipped through somehow. It's fixed.
